cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.SI

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a novel algorithm for online matrix factorization recommendation that combines linear bandits and alternating least squares. It also evaluates the performance of the proposed algorithm using cumulative regret and average cumulative NDCG. 

It could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as the problem being addressed is online collaborative filtering, which is a common task in information retrieval. 

Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it proposes an algorithm that uses machine learning techniques to make recommendations. 

It could also be classified under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it proposes a new algorithm for online matrix factorization recommendation. 

Finally, it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as collaborative filtering is a common task in social networks and the proposed algorithm could be applied in such settings.
